# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and paste your FastNEAR API key.
# Grab one from the FastNEAR dashboard; keeps us off the anonymous rate-limit
# ladder while we're hammering EXPERIMENTAL_tx_status / archival during the
# yield/resume mapping work.
#
# Use from shell:
#   set -a && source .env && set +a
#   curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $FASTNEAR_API_KEY" \
#        https://rpc.testnet.fastnear.com -d '{...}'
#   # or as a query param:
#   curl "https://rpc.testnet.fastnear.com/?apiKey=$FASTNEAR_API_KEY" -d '{...}'
#
# Frontend picks the key up one of two ways (either works; localStorage wins):
#   1. Copy web/config.example.js → web/config.local.js and paste the key there.
#   2. Paste it into the "FastNEAR API key" input in the Config section at
#      runtime; stored in localStorage under `FASTNEAR_API_KEY`.
#
# Testnet regular RPC retention is ~3 epochs (~21 h); older hashes fail over
# to https://archival-rpc.testnet.fastnear.com — the key applies to both.
#
# The internal `scripts/*.mjs` observability tools auto-load `.env`, so for the
# common local workflow you do not need to `source` it manually first.
FASTNEAR_API_KEY=
